Package: blacklight
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.1), coreutils, curl, jq, ${misc:Depends}
Description: blacklight — agent-directed defensive forensics for Linux
 blacklight is a single-file bash wrapper directed by a skills-native
 Managed Agent. It supercharges fifteen years of Linux OSS defensive
 primitives (iptables, mod_security, ClamAV, LMD, APF, YARA, Apache
 logs, .htaccess walks, crontab audits) with an always-on curator that
 persists case state across sim-days. No platform buy-in. No fleet
 migration.
